@startuml
title Serverless Computing for IoT - Data Flow Sequence Diagram

actor "IoT Device" as IoT
participant "RabbitMQ\n(AMQP/MQTT Broker)" as Broker
participant "Nuclio\n(Serverless Platform)" as Nuclio
participant "Producer Function\n(Event Generator)" as Producer
participant "Consumer Function\n(Event Processor)" as Consumer
participant "Logger" as Logger

== AMQP Data Flow ==

IoT -> Broker: Send temperature data\n(AMQP protocol)
activate Broker

Broker -> Nuclio: Trigger event
activate Nuclio

Nuclio -> Producer: Deploy and invoke\namqpevent function
activate Producer

Producer -> Broker: Publish temperature event\nto AMQP queue
deactivate Producer

Broker -> Nuclio: Queue message available
Nuclio -> Consumer: Deploy and invoke\namqpconsume function
activate Consumer

Consumer -> Broker: Consume message from queue
Broker --> Consumer: Temperature data
deactivate Broker

Consumer -> Consumer: Process temperature data
Consumer -> Logger: Forward processed data
activate Logger
Logger -> Logger: Log to console
deactivate Logger
deactivate Consumer
deactivate Nuclio

== MQTT Data Flow ==

IoT -> Broker: Publish temperature data\n(MQTT protocol)
activate Broker

Broker -> Nuclio: Trigger event
activate Nuclio

Nuclio -> Producer: Deploy and invoke\nmqttrandomevent function
activate Producer

Producer -> Broker: Publish random temperature\nto MQTT topic
deactivate Producer

Broker -> Nuclio: Topic message available
Nuclio -> Consumer: Deploy and invoke\nmqttconsume function
activate Consumer

Consumer -> Broker: Subscribe and consume\nfrom MQTT topic
Broker --> Consumer: Temperature data
deactivate Broker

Consumer -> Consumer: Process temperature data
Consumer -> Logger: Forward processed data
activate Logger
Logger -> Logger: Log to console
deactivate Logger
deactivate Consumer
deactivate Nuclio

@enduml
